Triple Net (NNN):
A lease in which the tenant is responsible for
all expenses associated with their proportional
share of occupancy of the building
Core:
Occupancy is greater than or equal to 90%
at time of sale
Value-Add:
Occupancy is greater than or equal to 60%
and less than 90% at time of sale
Opportunistic:
Occupancy is less than 60% at time of sale
